<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!DOCTYPE suppressions PUBLIC
        "-//Checkstyle//DTD SuppressionFilter Configuration 1.2//EN"
        "https://checkstyle.org/dtds/suppressions_1_2.dtd">
<!--
  Checkstyle's de-facto file baseline (Chapter 39, lever 3), read by the SuppressionFilter wired in
  checkstyle.xml. Each <suppress> row freezes a named check over a file path, so a noisy legacy file is
  tolerated without weakening the rule for the whole project.

  This file is intentionally empty of rows: the legacy code in this module is held clean for Checkstyle
  and carries only a SpotBugs finding (baselined in the SpotBugs filter), so the mechanism is wired and
  inert here — the exact place a real legacy file would be frozen. A frozen row would read, for example:

    <suppress checks="ConstantName" files="LegacyPriceTable\.java"/>

  and, like every baseline, would be reviewed in the PR and periodically retired rather than left to
  accumulate — debt about debt, not a permanent exemption.
-->
<suppressions>
</suppressions>
